    <example>
     <statement>
        <p>
           Find the Surface area of the triangular prism below. 
        </p> 
        <image width="50%">  
        <latex-image label="tikkz-prism-immage">
           \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1.2, font=\small, rotate=90]

                <!-- % Define colors
                \definecolor{faceblue}{RGB}{173, 216, 230}
                \definecolor{facegray}{RGB}{200, 200, 200}
                \definecolor{facegreen}{RGB}{180, 238, 180} -->

                % Coordinates
                \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
                \coordinate (B) at (3,0);
                \coordinate (C) at (1.5,2);
                \coordinate (D) at (1,-1.2);
                \coordinate (E) at (4,-1.2);
                \coordinate (F) at (2.5,0.8);

                % Draw prism faces
                % Back triangle
                \draw[thick] (D) -- (E) -- (F) -- cycle;
                % Bottom rectangle
                \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (E) -- (D) -- cycle;
                % Side rectangle
                \draw[thick] (B) -- (C) -- (F) -- (E) -- cycle;
                % Top rectangle
                \draw[thick] (C) -- (A) -- (D) -- (F) -- cycle;
                % Front triangle
                \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;

                % Labels on front triangle
                \node[left] at (A) {A};
                \node[right] at (B) {B};
                \node[above] at (C) {C};
                 \draw[dashed] (A) --(1.5,0);
                % Labels on back triangle
                \node[left] at (D) {D};
                \node[right] at (E) {E};
                \node[above] at (F) {F};

                % Optional edge labels
                \node[below] at ($(A)!0.5!(B)$) {8 cm};
                \node[left] at ($(A)!0.5!(C)$) {3 cm};
                \node[right] at ($(B)!0.5!(E)$) {12 cm};

                
            \end{tikzpicture}
        </latex-image>
        </image>
     </statement>
     <solution>
        <p>
           Step 1: Find the area of the base. 
        </p>
        <p>
            The triangle has a slant height of 5 cm and base 8cm. Using pythagorean relationship height i:
            <md>
                <mrow> = \amp \sqrt{25 \, \text{cm} -16\, \text{cm}} = 3\, \text{cm}</mrow>
                <mrow> \text{area of a triangle} = \amp \frac{1}{2}\times b \times h</mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp (\frac{1}{2} \times  3\, \text{cm} \times 8 \,\text{cm} ) \times 12\, \text{cm} </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp 144  \,\text{cm}^2</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
           Step 2: Multiply the area of the base by the height of the solid to find the volume 
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>\text{volume} = \amp  \text{area of base} \times \text{height}</mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp \frac{1}{2} b \times h \times H</mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp 48 \, \text{cm}^2 \times 12 \, \text{cm} </mrow>
                <mrow> \amp 576 \, \text{cm}^3</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            The surface of the triangular prism is <m>576 \, \text{cm}^3</m>.
        </p>
     </solution>
    </example>   
